# Realtime game server for the two-player Games arcade.
#
# Leave this UNSET to use the zero-config LAN default: the frontend connects to
# ws://<the-host-you-opened-the-site-on>:8080. Run the backend with
# `make backend-dev` (from repo root) and open the site on your machine's LAN
# IP from both phones/iPads.
#
# Set it to your deployed server for play over the internet (http→ws, https→wss
# is derived automatically):
# VITE_GAMES_SERVER_URL=https://games.your-domain.com
#
# Production — do not commit real URLs here. Set on the Railway frontend service:
#   VITE_GAMES_SERVER_URL=https://${{backend.RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}}

# --- Supabase (optional) ---------------------------------------------------
# Durable arcade data: profiles, leaderboards, match history, achievements,
# persistent rooms, friends, daily challenges. Leave UNSET for zero-config LAN
# play — the arcade still works, those features just switch off.
#
# Create a project at https://supabase.com, enable Anonymous sign-ins, apply
# the SQL in ../supabase/ (see supabase/README.md), then set:
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-ref.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key
#
# Only the anon PUBLIC key belongs here — never the service-role key.
